    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.7-10_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Manderson
                        <hi rend="caps">S.</hi> Dakota
                        June 4, 1936
                    </dateline>
                    
                    Mr John <hi rend="caps">G</hi> Neihardt
                
                    <salute>Dear John</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Its a long time since you heard from me. But first of all please pardon me for not <unclear>ans</unclear> you any sooner. I guess I have <unclear>kept</unclear> you <unclear>a</unclear> guessing &#8212;</p>
                
                <p>We have been unfortuned to have such <unclear>lucks</unclear> during this hard time&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>Hard times sure hit us also in health.</p>
                
                <p>My wife just got out of the Hospital couple weeks now she has been there darn near 3 months. She has been to every hospital in the state darn near it
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.7-10_0002a"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="authorial">2</fw>
                    she was in confinement case but she got injured before hand and she had to go before hand.</p>
                
                <p>That <add>left</add> me + the kids at home one of them had <unclear>Pnemonia</unclear> at the same time and about the same time my father got run over in a wagon. Horses ran away with him had 2 ribs broken.</p>
                
                <p>That was tough luck. Of course we all had to have help so I went and spent the <unclear>$44</unclear>.56 of <unclear>yours</unclear> But I know I could pay for bottles of part of Jelly <unclear/> is why I <unclear>don't</unclear> they I got a $68.00 coming but I hasn't got it yet. At the present writing
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.7-10_0002b"/>
               
                <fw type="authorial">3</fw>
                    we are all <hi rend="caps">OK</hi>. Father got well but he <del>don't</del> aint the old man he used to be.</p>
                
                <p>After all my wife brought home a baby boy and we call him John Neihardt Black Elk and we are proud of him to name him after a big man. Hope he will <add>be</add> good as you are. I will tell you some thing <del><hi rend="caps">E.A.</hi> Hawk</del> <del/></p>
                    
                <p>Emil <hi rend="caps">A</hi> Hawk has been loading the old man about lots of things. The old man felt uneasy for a while But he is perfectly satisfied very glad to hear you are coming again of course I have a place ready for you
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.7-10_0003"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <fw type="authorial">4</fw>
                    
                    Standing Bear + the old man are ready for you. We have been practising singing all kinds of songs. I also seen the fellow that could do Indian Conjuring make some sounds but he cant make spirits appear.</p>
                    
                <p>Everybody out here are anxious about your coming write <unclear>soon</unclear> tell us when you are coming</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Cousin</salute>
                    <signed><unclear>Benj</unclear> B Elk</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>"Old man is and <unclear>anxious</unclear> for you.</p></postscript>
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.7-10_0004"/>  
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                    
                    <note type="recipient">From Ben Black Elk, son of Black Elk, the holy man.</note> 
                
            </div1>
